<br>
Our first proposal - which  did not ask for more dates - was shot down so we tried a new approach.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukaradin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Karadin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Toede</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(11/15/00 4:39:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Errr..</span><hr size=1> No Aegirson, that is not what you are saying.  You are not aiming for a system based on numbers - you are basing it on some elistist notion that there are First Class and Second Class entities.  Simply stating something as a fact, does not make it so.<br>
<br>
You are not saying that any guild with 80 people should have twice as much time as a guild with 40 members.  You are saying Five guilds are seen by you as equals and are somehow superior to other guilds.   KEG/BOTS/CIW/MFH/FOR are the guilds you find &quot;worthy&quot; of getting extra days.  It's not up to you or those five guilds to decide what scraps the rest of us get.<br>
<br>
For one thing, your guild as posted on Rewena's list has 75 people - my alliance has 69.  RoS has 75, SoT is close at 63.  Certainly more than 40.  Yet the proposal only says these Five &quot;Class A&quot; entities get extra days.  Sorry, the elitism won't fly.  You are our equal, not our superior.  You choose to have a guild that has 75 members, I choose to be in an Alliance of 69, even though NH has 40 of its own members.  We live with those decisions - you want a guild of 90 so be it, you want a guild of 30, then deal with that decision.  Neither of us is &quot;entitled&quot; to more days than the other, neither based on accomplishments nor on numbers.  As you and Sukar like to say - don't make this communism.  It's not per person plane time, it's per guild - always has been.<br>
<br>
Under the current proposal that the vast majority support (i.e. one day raids in Fear/Hate for EVERYONE), we ALL get to go to the planes more often than once a month.  At 40 members per entity, we have 16 valid posting entities.  That is enough that almost EVERY entity gets two, ONE day raids per month per plane.  And no one has to be an elitist about it.<br>
